I look forward to meeting with you both on Tuesday.  Here's a list of the

funds we have in the pipeline and the status:


MACRO FUNDS-

1.Harvard (Docs done)- We have been dealing with them in crude, products, and

natural gas- we just need to keep track of their credit line.


2. Tudor- we have docs with Ospraie, Tudor Proprietary, Tudor Offshore

(Bermuda)- dealing regularly..


3. Catequil (Negotiating) docs with Offshore and Onshore- waiting for

response from Brent and Paul on their latest comments to the ISDA.  Confirms

from all the deals we have done have been returned to Carol.  They are set up

in the system; we hold margin.


4. AIG (Negotiating)- Offshore, Onshore- need to get documents out to them-

credit work sheet in legal.. still have not gotten out a confirm to them on

the trades they have done....we have them set up in the system and hold

margin.


5. Union Spring (Negotiating)- Offshore, Onshore- should be done on this one.


6. SAC Capital - possibly only one vehicle in Anguila- need to get the

document to them- credit work sheet in legal.


7. Quark Power (Negotiating)- 2 entities- Quark Power and Amaranth.  Held by

Paloma Partners- waiting for their comments on a few points.


8. Valentis and CD Holdings- Held by Wexford Capital - need to get document

to them- credit work sheet in legal.  They want to proceed with the 8 year

deal Monday.


9. Global Advisors- trade through Cargill.. Frank Sayre working on POA..

waiting for this back.


10. Argonaut- onshore, offshore vehicles- sending documents.. no credit

assessment yet.


11. SOROS- brought through system by credit derivative group.. but need a

credit opinion for ENA (to do energy trades).


PROGRAM FUNDS-

12. Renaissance - credit worksheet in legal- need to get docs to them.

13. Campbell+ Co - will likely want to look at a three way transaction

between Enron, themselves, and a bank

14. Sunrise Capital - getting documentation.
